	abstract = {Many pest species exhibit huge fluctuations in population abundance. Understanding their large‐scale and long‐term dynamics is necessary to develop effective control and management strategies. Occupancy models represent a promising approach to unravel interactions between environmental factors and spatiotemporal dynamics of outbreaking populations. Here, we investigated population dynamics of the Australian plague locust,
